When you speak to the universe, the entire world becomes at peace, all commotion disappears. The whole universe at once becomes tranquil. Not a sound is to be heard, only the rustling leaves among the trees. Take a look at the trailer for "Beginner's Mind," the seventh episode in the second season of "Poetry Sans Frontiers." Featuring 23 Chinese and foreign guests from 16 different countries, the second season began on January 1. It has seven episodes: Friendship, Life, Dream, Courage, Peace, Return and Beginner's Mind. The featured guests are poets, dramatists, dancers, drummers, war journalists, former U.S. soldiers, Syrian refugees, mountaineers, navigators, translators, doctors, teachers and farm women with terminal illnesses who love poetry. Listen to their poems and their heartwarming stories.